  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In Sect. 3, we describe the use of lensed SNe as an astrophysical probe, such as constraining the SN progenitors and dust in galaxies.",
    "In Sect. 4, we present various searches of lensed SNe and the expected rates in current and upcoming surveys.",
    "We summarise in Sect. 5.",
    "While the idea of using lensed SNe for measuring the Hubble constant dates back to Refsdal (1964), this time-delay method was first realised with lensed quasars that were discovered decades before lensed SNe, starting with the first lensed quasar system found by Walsh et al. (1979).",
    "The use of lensed quasars as a cosmological probe is reviewed by Birrer et al. (2024) in this collection (see also, e.g., Treu and Marshall 2016; Suyu et al. 2018; Treu et al. 2022)."
  ],
